CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 9, 1966, pg. 16A, reads: "Champs Honored - The 'Big Seven' of the Schenley High School state championship basketball team were on hand at City Hall last week where they were honored by Mayor Joe Barr and members of City Council for their outstanding cage season. Mayor Barr is shown shaking hands with All State performer Kenny Durrett as other members of the team and Commission John McGrady look on.  Other Schenley players, from left, are Jim Prince, Ed Gibson, Montel Brundage, Jake Williams, Marvin Snowden and Charley Burley...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School state champion basketball players and city officials, including left to right: Kenny Durrett shaking hands with mayor, James "Jim" Prince, Pittsburgh Mayor Joseph M. Barr, Edward "Petey" Gibson, Montel Brundage, Commissioner John McGrady, Jacob "Jake" H. Williams, Jr., Marvin Snowden, and Charles "Charley" Burley Jr., in Pittsburgh City Council Chambers, City County Building
